# @blen/ctgov-mcp — example environment configuration.
#
# Copy to `.env` and edit. Nothing in here is secret today (the embedded AS
# users come from this file for self-hosts; everything else is public
# metadata). When you deploy behind Clerk / WorkOS / Auth0, the AS takes
# over and no credentials live here.
#
# Usage:
#   cp .env.example .env
#   # edit values, then:
#   export $(grep -v '^#' .env | xargs)
#   node dist/bin.js --http
#
# Reference: README.md → "Configuration reference".

# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Transport / runtime
# ------------------------------------------------------------------

# HTTP bind (used with --http). Ignored for stdio.
PORT=8080
HOST=0.0.0.0

# Log verbosity: debug | info | warn | error
CTGOV_LOG_LEVEL=info

# Sandbox selection: isolate | deno | auto
# Equivalent to `--sandbox`. Leave as auto in most cases.
CTGOV_SANDBOX=auto

# Optional: explicit path to the deno binary used by the fallback executor.
# Only needed if `deno` isn't on PATH.
# CTGOV_DENO_PATH=/usr/local/bin/deno

# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Auth (required for --http unless you pass --insecure for dev)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------

# One of: none | clerk | workos | auth0 | generic-oidc | embedded
# `none`     — no auth; stdio only, or --insecure in dev.
# `clerk`    — production default. Also the shape used by workos/auth0/generic-oidc.
# `embedded` — self-hosted AS built into this server (RFC 7591 DCR + PKCE).
CTGOV_AUTH_PROVIDER=none

# The authorization server's issuer URL.
#   Clerk:    https://clerk.<your-domain>
#   WorkOS:   https://api.workos.com/user_management/<client_id>
#   Auth0:    https://<tenant>.us.auth0.com
#   Embedded: the same public URL where THIS server is reachable
# CTGOV_AUTH_ISSUER=https://clerk.blencorp.com

# Optional JWKS override. When unset, defaults to:
#   ${CTGOV_AUTH_ISSUER}/.well-known/jwks.json  (all OIDC providers)
#   ${CTGOV_AUTH_ISSUER}/as/jwks.json           (embedded)
# CTGOV_AUTH_JWKS_URL=

# RFC 8707 audience / our advertised `resource` identifier.
# Must match where this server is actually reachable behind TLS.
CTGOV_AUTH_RESOURCE=https://mcp.clinicaltrial.blencorp.com/mcp

# Scopes advertised in PRM and requested at /authorize.
CTGOV_AUTH_SCOPES=ctgov.read

# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Embedded AS — only used when CTGOV_AUTH_PROVIDER=embedded
# ------------------------------------------------------------------

# HTTP Basic credentials resolved during /as/authorize.
# Format: "user1:pass1,user2:pass2". Never commit real credentials.
# CTGOV_EMBEDDED_USERS=alice:wonderland,bob:builder

# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Tests / scripts
# ------------------------------------------------------------------

# Set to 1 to enable test/liveIntegration.spec.ts (hits the real CT.gov API).
# CTGOV_LIVE=1

# Override the upstream base URL used by the regen/verify scripts.
# Useful for testing against a staging mirror.
# CTGOV_BASE=https://clinicaltrials.gov/api/v2

# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Reminders
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# - Never commit .env with real values.
# - For Claude Connectors Directory submission, CTGOV_AUTH_PROVIDER MUST NOT
#   be `none`. Use `clerk` (recommended) or `embedded` with TLS.
# - ClinicalTrials.gov enforces ~10 req/sec globally. The server rate-limits
#   to stay under this; no extra tuning needed.
